# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Airtight ignore policy
#
# This working folder also contains large, PRIVATE data files (multi-GB
# .rar archives and data sub-folders) that must NEVER be committed.
# To make leaks impossible, we ignore EVERYTHING by default and then
# explicitly whitelist only the files that belong in this repository.
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# 1) Ignore everything
*

# 2) ...but keep the project files
!.gitignore
!README.md
!LICENSE
!whatsapp_chat_viewer.py

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Safety net (redundant with the rule above, kept for clarity/intent)
# Never track generated output, private archives, or Python caches.
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Generated by the script at runtime
chat_data/
chat_viewer.html

# Private / large data — keep out of version control
*.rar
*.zip
*.7z
*.tar
*.gz

# Python
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*.egg-info/
.venv/
venv/
env/

# OS / editor noise
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
.idea/
.vscode/
.claude/
